s (approx. 1 in.). Place shell pieces and butter into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> and sauté <b>5 min\/212°F\/speed 0.5<b>."},{"content":"Add wine and cognac and without measuring cup cook <b>5 min\/212°F\/speed 0.5<b>."},{"content":"Add onions, carrots, celery, leeks, garlic, thyme and parsley and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add reserved water and seafood stock. Place simmering basket on top of mixing bowl lid and cook <b>30 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>. <strong>Insert simmering basket<\/strong> and holding in place with spatula, strain liquid into a pitcher then strain again through a fine sieve (or 4 layers of cheesecloth) into a bowl.  Press remaining contents with spatula to extract as much liquid as possible. Discard solids, reserve broth and rinse mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place strained broth, rice, tomato paste, salt, pepper and cayenne into mixing bowl and cook with simmering basket on top of mixing bowl lid <b>20 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>. Blend <b>1 min\/speed 8<b> increasing speed gradually."},{"content":"Add cream and reserved lobster meat into mixing bowl and mix <b>1 min\/speed 1<b>. Divide bisque between 4 bowls and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To remove lobster meat from shells: cut the cooked lobster tails lengthwise, loosen the meat with fingers and pull it out in one whole section.","Serve bisque with chopped fresh herbs (e.g. chives, parsley or tarragon) and sliced buttered sourdough or fresh baguette."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 50m","4 portions"]}